name: Misal Pav
summary: Misal Pav is spicy dish in western indian state
description: It consists of misal (a spicy curry usually made from moth beans) and pav (a type of Indian bread roll).[1][2] The final dish is topped with farsan or sev, onions, lemon and coriander (cilantro).
